>$</span>245.00</bdi></span></a></div><div><a href=\\\"/search?q=ilve+g4221208\\\"><div><img loading=\\\"lazy\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/G4221208_p16378-1.jpg\\\" width=\\\"115\\\"/></div><div>ILVE G4221208 Scroll Claw Leg (Sold by Individual Leg) (Chrome)</div><span><bdi><span>$</span>242.00</bdi></span></a></div><div><a href=\\\"/search?q=ilve+kgset001\\\"><div><img loading=\\\"lazy\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/KGSET001_p20076.jpg\\\" width=\\\"115\\\"/></div><div>ILVE KGSET001 Total Extension Glide Racks</div><span><bdi><span>$</span>168.00</bdi></span></a></div></div> </div> </div> </div> \", \"Option1 Name\": \"Color\", \"Option1 Value\": \"Burgundy\", \"Option2 Name\": \"Trim\", \"Option2 Value\": \"Burnished\", \"Option3 Name\": \"Oven Door Type\", \"Option3 Value\": \"Triple Glass Door\"}, {\"Variant Name\": \"ILVE - 40 inch Majestic II Induction Range with 6 Elements, Booster Function, Bridge Control, Residual Heat Indicator (Burgundy / Chrome / Triple Glass Door) - UMDI10NS3BUC\", \"Variant SKU\": \"UMDI10NS3BUC\", \"Variant Image\": \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/UMDI10NS3BUC_p13674.jpg\", \"Variant All Images\": [\"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/UMDI10NS3BUC_p13674.jpg\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/UMDI10NS3BUC_p13674_173297.png\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/UMDI10NS3BUC_p13674_173298.png\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/UMDI10NS3BUC_p13674_173299.png\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/UMDI10NS3BUC_p13674_11294.jpg\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/UMDI10NS3BUC_p13674_11295.jpg\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/UMDI10NS3BUC_p13674_11296.jpg\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/UMDI10NS3BUC_p13674_11297.jpg\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/UMDI10NS3BUC_p13674_33116.jpg\"], \"Variant Price\": \"9990.00\", \"Variant Barcode\": \"8051202193344\", \"Variant URLS\": \"\", \"Variant Count\": \"\", \"Variant HTML\": \" <div aria-hidden=\\\"true\\\" aria-labelledby=\\\"station-tabs-tab_description\\\" class=\\\"station-tabs-tabpanel station-tabs-default-tabpanel\\\" id=\\\"station-tabs-tabpanel_description\\\" role=\\\"tabpanel\\\"> <div class=\\\"station-tabs-tabcontent\\\"><div class=\\\"station-tabs-tabcontent\\\"><p>Classic Italian design meets state-of-the-art technology in the Majestic 40-inch induction range, which boasts six efficient element zones, a total oven capacity of 2.3 + 1.52 cu. ft., a 4.3-inch full-touch control display, and an enamel oven cavity that is easy to clean.</p><p>Order now for delivery in 90 to 120 days!</p><div><p><strong>Majestic</strong></p><p>The show-stopping range cooker that will turn your kitchen into a showpiece.</p><p></p><p>Majestic is a freestanding statement-piece that exudes elegance and functionality in equal measure. Its design draws inspiration from the world of professional cooking and features rounded lines, crafted details, fine finishes, and solutions and technologies. Despite its ability to blend into any setting, Majestic commands attention.</p><p></p><p>The graceful curves and meticulously crafted details of majestic range cookers make them beautiful additions to any home.</p><p></p><p>These are the real deal, hand-picked gems of professional design for your home kitchen. They come in a variety of sizes (from 30 to 60 inches) and offer a plethora of set-up options, as well as RAL Classic shades upon request and fine metallic finishes.</p><p></p><ul><li>Heat indicator with residual</li><li>Effortless stopwatch</li><li>Control of bridges</li><li>Enhancement feature</li><li>Controls that slide</li><li>Preventing harm to children</li><li>Widescreen 4.3-inch</li><li>Emergency measures for overheating and liquid spills</li><li>Accurate electronic regulation of temperature</li><li>Cabinet and door soft-closing mechanism</li><li>Fast start</li></ul><p></p><hr/><p></p><p><strong>Technology for Products</strong></p><p></p><p>When it comes to cooking, form follows function. ILVE puts its knowledge and expertise to work for you, providing solutions that combine high-level performance with maximum simplicity, safety, and user-friendliness, ensuring the highest level of satisfaction at all times.</p><p></p><p><strong>Technologies for the Kitchen Range</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>Dual-Platform Induction Cooktop</strong></p><p>With their modern technology and elegant design, Majestic induction cooktops (hobs) make cooking a breeze. Induction offers many benefits, such as safe cooking, reduced energy consumption, safety, adjustable temperature control, and quick cooking times, all of which make it easier to prepare dishes and recipes.</p><p></p><p><strong>Measurement of Persistent Heat</strong></p><p>The glass is hot, so be careful not to touch it or put anything on it; doing so could cause damage.</p><p></p><p><strong>Stop-Starting Timer</strong></p><p>Once the specified time has passed, the active zone is disabled.</p><p></p><p><strong>Control of Bridges</strong></p><p>If your induction cooktop (hob) has this capability, you can treat two adjacent zones as one and use a single command to control them both.</p><p></p><p><strong>Enhancement Role</strong></p><p>Makes it possible to concentrate the entire induction burner's power on a specific area, allowing you to boil and cook food more quickly.</p><p></p><p><strong>Slide Handles</strong></p><p>For instance, you can adjust the operating temperature simply by gliding your finger from right to left or left to right thanks to this convenient \\\"touch control\\\" system.</p><p></p><p><strong>Protecting Children</strong></p><p>The induction cooktop (hob) cannot be turned on using the controls once this feature has been enabled and will remain so until disabled.</p><p></p><p><strong>Protecting Against Overheating and Liquid Spills</strong></p><p>An automatic shutoff mechanism activates in the event of a liquid spill or overheating of the cooktop (hob).</p><p></p><hr/><p></p><p><strong>Oven Solutions</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>The Ovens: Massive Capacity and Peak Efficiency.</strong></p><p>We have a 40-inch range with a capacity of up to 4 cubic feet, so you can choose between a single or double combination oven that will give you plenty of room, even for big dishes.</p><p></p><p><strong>Accurate Electronic Regulation of Temperature</strong></p><p>In contrast to traditional ovens, which experience temperature fluctuations, the electronic control keeps the oven temperature constant the whole time.</p><p></p><p><strong>A 4.3-inch Full-Touch Screen</strong></p><p>The screen guarantees excellent legibility with TFT technology, showing every function with clear and immediate graphics.</p><p></p><p><strong>TFT Screen; Easy to Use, Extensive, and High-Resolution.</strong></p><p>With a single touch of the big screen, you can control all the features of either the single oven or both ovens simultaneously. You can set the temperature, set the timer, and program the ovens to start and stop cooking automatically.</p><p></p><p><strong>Doors with a Gentle Closing Mechanism</strong></p><p>A shock absorber is integrated into the door hinges, allowing for a quieter and more gradual closing.</p><p></p><p><strong>Drawer Warmer with Soft-Closing Mechanism</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>The Cooking Probe</strong></p><p>The tool you need to check the internal temperature of meat, among other things.</p><p></p><p><strong>Steam Ejection (Hot Food Preparation)</strong></p><p>With this system, the vapours are drawn out from within the cavity, giving you the option for a more or less moist cooking, so you can get a crunchy baked dish or a juicy roast.</p><p></p><p><strong>Heat range: 85 to 575 degrees Fahrenheit</strong></p><p>No matter how complicated or intricate your recipe is, an ILVE oven can effortlessly and perfectly complete every step, from proofing to cooking, roasting to low temperature.</p><p></p><p><strong>Using High Density Insulation and Tangential Cooling Ventilation</strong></p><p>Shields kitchen and oven-related furniture from dangerously high temperatures.</p><p></p><p><strong>The Ultimate Cleaning Solution: A Folding Grill Coil</strong></p><p>The electric heating element of the grill can be lowered for easier cleaning of the top part of the cavity, thanks to the articulated support.</p><p></p><p><strong>Dishwasher Safe Enamel</strong></p><p>Because the grease doesn't adhere to the surface, it's easier to clean.</p><p></p><p><strong>Essential Oven Operations. UOV 60 E3 TFT S</strong></p><p></p><ul><li>Pizza party</li><li>Removing From Freeze</li><li>Intensive culinary</li><li>Getting started quickly</li><li>Extremely moist cooking</li><li>Grilling with a fan</li><li>Cooking on the grill with the door closed</li><li>Aerial cuisine</li><li>Wet cooking with an overhead fan</li><li>Using the ground up</li><li>Cooking with moisture from below</li><li>Regular, static cooking</li><li>Static, moist, typical cooking</li><li>Using a number of fans to cook</li><li>Various wet fan cooking methods</li><li>Sustainable cuisine</li></ul><p></p><p><strong>Functions of the Secondary Oven. UOV 30 E3 TFT</strong></p><p></p><ul><li>Grilling in a covered area</li><li>Aerial cuisine</li><li>Using the ground up</li><li>Standard, unchanging cooking</li><li>Sustainable cuisine</li></ul><hr/><p></p><p><strong>A Pizza Party</strong></p><p>This oven is perfect for baking pizza, bread, focaccia, and other similar foods. The lower heating element is the primary heat source, and it works in tandem with the other, less powerful heating elements to provide the ideal conditions for baking.</p><p></p><p><strong>Removing from Freeze</strong></p><p>Guarantees rapid thawing of any and all frozen foods, bringing them to room temperature without changing their flavor or texture.</p><p></p><p><strong>Cooking to the Extremes</strong></p><p>For foods that require a crispy finish, such as baked potatoes and veggies, chicken, salt-crusted fish, etc., this steam-discharge method guarantees rapid and intense cooking.</p><p></p><p><strong>Accelerated Learning</strong></p><p>Fast preheating gets you to the temperature you want quickly, and then you can select the cooking mode that's going to work best for your food. When set to low heat, it can also defrost food quickly.</p><p></p><p><strong>Thoroughly Moist Cooking</strong></p><p>For moist cooking, such as braised meat, stewed rabbit, salt cod, chicken cacciatore, etc., it ensures rapid and intense cooking with steam block.</p><p></p><p><strong>Grilling with a Fan</strong></p><p>Many foods, including sausages, pork or mixed kebabs, game, Roman-style gnocchi, etc., can be cooked quickly and thoroughly with this function, which also significantly reduces energy consumption.</p><p></p><p><strong>Methods for Grilling with a Closed Door</strong></p><p>Ideal for searing fillets, Florentine steaks, fish, and even veggies quickly and thoroughly, as well as browning and roasting meat in general.</p><p></p><p><strong>Above-Ground Cooking</strong></p><p>Burgers, pork chops, veal steaks, sole, cuttlefish, etc., all benefit from browning and the finishing touch of color that this function provides.</p><p></p><p><strong>Delicately Cooked Food from Above</strong></p><p>Perfect for browning and finishing the color of a wide variety of foods without mushiness.</p><p></p><p><strong>Exploring the World of Home Cooking from Below</strong></p><p>In particular, for pastries (biscuits, meringues, leavened desserts, fruit desserts, etc.), this is the best way to finish the cooking cycle.</p><p></p><p><strong>In-Depth Recipes for Moist Food</strong></p><p>In order to finish the cooking cycle with the correct amount of moisture, this is the best way to do it.</p><p></p><p><strong>Regular, Unchanging Cooking</strong></p><p>Pork chops, sausages, salt cod, braised meat, game, roast veal, meringues, biscuits, baked fruit, etc. are all great candidates for this electric oven's classic function.</p><p></p><p><strong>Normal Cooking with Moist Static</strong></p><p>This makes traditional static cooking even more moist.</p><p></p><p><strong>Multi-Fan Oven Utilization</strong></p><p>You can bake a variety of foods at once without worrying about their aromas blending\\u2014lasagna, croissants and brioches, tarts, cakes, etc.\\u2014and save both time and energy thanks to this feature.</p><p></p><p><strong>A Variety of Moist Fan Recipes</strong></p><p>When cooking with multiple fans, this increases the moisture content.</p><p></p><p><strong>Sustainable Food Preparation</strong></p><p>With the ECO function, cooking times adapt to slow roasting, like braised meats, white meats, baked pasta, delicate pastries, and so on. This cooking cycle is not meant for frozen foods, but it does allow for significant savings on electricity consumption.</p><p></p><p><strong>Proposition 65 in California\\u2014</strong></p><p>CAUTIONS: Potential Cancer and Reproductive Risks</p><p><a href=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/.\\\" rel=\\\"noopener\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">Visit www.P65Warnings.ca.gov for more information.</a></p></div> <div><div> <div> <video controls=\\\"\\\" preload=\\\"auto\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/qIZ8MSDCu-Y.mp4\\\" style=\\\"max-width:320px; margin-bottom:1.2rem;\\\">Sorry, but the video tag isn't compatible with your browser.</video> </div> <div> <video controls=\\\"\\\" preload=\\\"auto\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/RRQlYvQPAMg.mp4\\\" style=\\\"max-width:320px; margin-bottom:1.2rem;\\\">There is a problem with the video tag in your browser.</video> </div> <div> <video controls=\\\"\\\" preload=\\\"auto\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/Uh_EEzfUhUU.mp4\\\" style=\\\"max-width:320px; margin-bottom:1.2rem;\\\">The video tag is not supported by your browser.</video> </div> <div> <video controls=\\\"\\\" preload=\\\"auto\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/wKi6ZYNcCxY.mp4\\\" style=\\\"max-width:320px; margin-bottom:1.2rem;\\\">The video tag is not supporte