mg loading=\\\"lazy\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/G04001_p16241-1.jpg\\\" width=\\\"115\\\"/></div><div>ILVE G/040/01 Griddle Dome</div><span><bdi><span>$</span>245.00</bdi></span></a></div><div><a href=\\\"/search?q=ilve+g4221208\\\"><div><img loading=\\\"lazy\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/G4221208_p16378-1.jpg\\\" width=\\\"115\\\"/></div><div>ILVE G4221208 Scroll Claw Leg (Sold by Individual Leg) (Chrome)</div><span><bdi><span>$</span>242.00</bdi></span></a></div><div><a href=\\\"/search?q=ilve+kgset001\\\"><div><img loading=\\\"lazy\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/KGSET001_p20076.jpg\\\" width=\\\"115\\\"/></div><div>ILVE KGSET001 Total Extension Glide Racks</div><span><bdi><span>$</span>168.00</bdi></span></a></div></div> </div> </div> </div> \", \"Option1 Name\": \"Color\", \"Option1 Value\": \"Stainless Steel\", \"Option2 Name\": \"Trim\", \"Option2 Value\": \"Chrome\", \"Option3 Name\": \"Oven Door Type\", \"Option3 Value\": \"Triple Glass Door\"}, {\"Variant Name\": \"ILVE - 40 inch Majestic II Induction Range with 6 Elements, Booster Function, Bridge Control, Residual Heat Indicator (Stainless Steel / Brass / Triple Glass Door) - UMDI10NS3SSG\", \"Variant SKU\": \"UMDI10NS3SSG\", \"Variant Image\": \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/UMDI10NS3SSG_p13710.jpg\", \"Variant All Images\": [\"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/UMDI10NS3SSG_p13710.jpg\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/UMDI10NS3SSG_p13710_173371.png\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/UMDI10NS3SSG_p13710_173372.png\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/UMDI10NS3SSG_p13710_173373.png\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/UMDI10NS3SSG_p13710_11394.jpg\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/UMDI10NS3SSG_p13710_11395.jpg\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/UMDI10NS3SSG_p13710_11396.jpg\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/UMDI10NS3SSG_p13710_11397.jpg\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/UMDI10NS3SSG_p13710_33137.jpg\"], \"Variant Price\": \"9990.00\", \"Variant Barcode\": \"8051202188104\", \"Variant URLS\": \"\", \"Variant Count\": \"\", \"Variant HTML\": \" <div aria-hidden=\\\"true\\\" aria-labelledby=\\\"station-tabs-tab_description\\\" class=\\\"station-tabs-tabpanel station-tabs-default-tabpanel\\\" id=\\\"station-tabs-tabpanel_description\\\" role=\\\"tabpanel\\\"> <div class=\\\"station-tabs-tabcontent\\\"><div class=\\\"station-tabs-tabcontent\\\"><p>The Majestic 40-inch induction range is a perfect example of how traditional Italian design can coexist with modern technology. It has six efficient element zones, two total oven capacities of 2.3 and 1.52 cubic feet, a 4.3-inch full-touch control display, and an enamel oven cavity that is easy to clean.</p><p>Currently Available: Yes</p><div><p><strong>Majestic</strong></p><p>This show-stopping range cooker will be the focal point of your kitchen.</p><p></p><p>Majestic is a freestanding statement-piece that effortlessly integrates into any space while commanding attention with its striking combination of form and function. Its design draws inspiration from the world of professional cooking and features rounded lines, crafted details, fine finishes, and solutions and technologies that are both practical and aesthetically pleasing.</p><p></p><p>The graceful curves and meticulously crafted details of majestic range cookers make them beautiful additions to any home.</p><p></p><p>Designed for your home's kitchen, these workhorses are available in a variety of colors (from 30 to 60 inches) and set-up options (from multiple options) and can be customized to RAL Classic shades upon request. They also feature fine metallic finishes.</p><p></p><ul><li>Signal for remaining heat</li><li>Automatically stops the timer</li><li>Manage bridges</li><li>Function that boosts</li><li>Handles for sliding</li><li>Protecting children</li><li>Widescreen 4.3-inch</li><li>Safeguarding against overheating and liquid leaks</li><li>Electronic temperature control with pinpoint accuracy</li><li>Drawer and door with a gentle closing mechanism</li><li>Fast start</li></ul><p></p><hr/><p></p><p><strong>Technology for Products</strong></p><p></p><p>Although aesthetics are important, having the best technologies available is essential for cooking well and enjoying oneself. ILVE offers solutions that combine top-level performance with maximum simplicity, safety, and user-friendliness, combining these factors to guarantee the best satisfaction.</p><p></p><p><strong>Technologies related to stovetops</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>Electric Range (Head)</strong></p><p>Majestic induction cooktops (hobs) are a modern, practical, and safe method of cooking that combines cutting-edge technology with an elegant and modern aesthetic. Induction offers many benefits, such as safety, ease of cleaning, energy savings, and versatile temperature control and cooking speed, all of which make it easier to prepare dishes and recipes.</p><p></p><p><strong>Detector of Remaining Heat</strong></p><p>Wear protective gloves and avoid touching or setting anything delicate on the glass because it is hot.</p><p></p><p><strong>Stop-Starting Timer</strong></p><p>At the end of the specified time, the active zone is disabled.</p><p></p><p><strong>Bridge Management</strong></p><p>If your induction cooktop (hob) has this capability, you can treat two adjacent zones as one and use a single command to control them both.</p><p></p><p><strong>Enhancement Role</strong></p><p>Puts the induction cooktop's (hob's) full power into the predetermined area, allowing you to boil and cook more quickly.</p><p></p><p><strong>Slide Handles</strong></p><p>For instance, you can adjust the operating temperature simply by gliding your finger from right to left or left to right thanks to this convenient \\\"touch control\\\" system.</p><p></p><p><strong>Protection of Children</strong></p><p>You can't use the controls to turn on the induction cooktop (hob) once this feature is enabled; it remains disabled until you disable it.</p><p></p><p><strong>Protecting Against Overheating and Liquid Spills</strong></p><p>An automatic shutoff mechanism activates in the event of a liquid spill or overheating of the cooktop (hob).</p><p></p><hr/><p></p><p><strong>Oven Solutions</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>Impressive Size and Power: The Ovens.</strong></p><p>Our 40-inch range offers an oven capacity of up to 4 cubic feet, so you'll have plenty of room for even the largest of dishes with any combination oven, single or double.</p><p></p><p><strong>Controlling Temperature with Electronic Precision</strong></p><p>The oven's temperature stays consistent throughout thanks to the electronic control, unlike with traditional ovens.</p><p></p><p><strong>Full-Screen 4.3-Inch Display</strong></p><p>Displaying every function with clear and immediate graphics, the display guarantees superior readability thanks to TFT technology.</p><p></p><p><strong>TFT Screen; Easy to Use, Extensive, and High-Resolution.</strong></p><p>With a single touch of the big screen, you can control all the features of either the single oven or both ovens simultaneously. You can set the temperature, set the timer, and program the ovens to start and stop cooking automatically.</p><p></p><p><strong>Smooth-Closing Door System</strong></p><p>With the shock absorber installed in the door hinges, closing the door is a more gradual and noiseless process.</p><p></p><p><strong>Soft-Closing Mechanism for the Warming Drawer</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>The Cooking Probe</strong></p><p>The tool you need to check the internal temperature of meat, among other things.</p><p></p><p><strong>Steam Ejection (Hot Food Preparation)</strong></p><p>With this system, the vapours are drawn out from within the cavity, giving you the option for a more or less moist cooking, so you can get a crunchy baked dish or a juicy roast.</p><p></p><p><strong>Heat range: 85 to 575 degrees Fahrenheit</strong></p><p>With an ILVE oven, you can effortlessly and perfectly prepare even the most intricate and sophisticated recipes, whether you're roasting, cooking, or proofing.</p><p></p><p><strong>Using High Density Insulation and Tangential Cooling Ventilation</strong></p><p>Makes sure that the kitchen and its furniture don't get too hot.</p><p></p><p><strong>Effortless Cleaning with the Folding Grill Coil</strong></p><p>The electric heating element of the grill can be lowered for easier cleaning of the top part of the cavity, thanks to the articulated support.</p><p></p><p><strong>Dishwasher Safe Enamel</strong></p><p>Because the grease doesn't adhere to the surface, it's easier to clean.</p><p></p><p><strong>Key Oven Responsibilities. UOV 60 E3 TFT S</strong></p><p></p><ul><li>Pizza party</li><li>Removing From Freeze</li><li>Prolonged cooking</li><li>Getting started quickly</li><li>Extremely moist cooking</li><li>Cooking with a fan grill</li><li>Cooking on the grill with the door closed</li><li>Making food from on high</li><li>Cooking with moisture from above</li><li>From the ground up, cook</li><li>Cooking with moisture from below</li><li>Basic, unchanging cooking</li><li>Normal cooking with moist static heat</li><li>Numerous fan-assisted cooking methods</li><li>Several wet fan ovens</li><li>Sustainable cuisine</li></ul><p></p><p><strong>Functions of the Secondary Oven. UOV 30 E3 TFT</strong></p><p></p><ul><li>Cooking on the grill with the door closed</li><li>Aerial cuisine</li><li>Starting with the base</li><li>Standard, unchanging cooking</li><li>Green food preparation</li></ul><hr/><p></p><p><strong>Party Pizza</strong></p><p>The lower heating element, in conjunction with the other, less powerful heating elements, produces the ideal temperature and baking conditions for pizza, bread, and focaccia.</p><p></p><p><strong>Removing from Freeze</strong></p><p>Ensures that any food that is frozen will defrost rapidly, bringing it to room temperature without changing its flavor or appearance.</p><p></p><p><strong>Extensive Preparation</strong></p><p>This steam-discharge cooker guarantees rapid and intense cooking and is ideal for foods that require a crunchy finish, such as baked potatoes and veggies, chicken, fish with a salt crust, etc.</p><p></p><p><strong>Accelerated Launch</strong></p><p>Quick preheating gets the oven to the temperature you want it to be in no time at all, and then you can select the cooking mode that's going to work best with your food. When set to a low temperature, it can also defrost food quickly.</p><p></p><p><strong>Thoroughly Moist Cooking</strong></p><p>For moist dishes like chicken cacciatore, braised meat, stewed rabbit, salt cod, etc., it guarantees rapid and intense cooking with steam block.</p><p></p><p><strong>Grilling with a Fan</strong></p><p>This function is great for a wide variety of foods because it is quick, deep, and uses a lot of energy. Some examples of these foods are sausages, pork or mixed kebabs, game, Roman-style gnocchi, and pork chops.</p><p></p><p><strong>Charcoal Grilling with a Closed Door</strong></p><p>Functions such as quick and deep grilling, browning, roasting, and cooking fillets, Florentine steaks, fish, and vegetables are highly recommended.</p><p></p><p><strong>Elevated Cooking</strong></p><p>Burgers, pork chops, veal steaks, sole, cuttlefish, etc., all benefit from browning and the finishing touch of color that this function provides.</p><p></p><p><strong>Delicately Cooked Food from Above</strong></p><p>Perfect for turning foods a golden brown while still keeping them tender, it also gives a variety of dishes their final color.</p><p></p><p><strong>The Art of Cooking from the Ground Up</strong></p><p>For pastries (biscuits, meringues, leavened desserts, fruit desserts, etc.), this is the best way to finish cooking the cycle.</p><p></p><p><strong>Healthy Recipes Made from Scratch</strong></p><p>This is the best way to finish the cooking cycle with the correct amount of moisture.</p><p></p><p><strong>Normal Static Cooking</strong></p><p>Pork chops, sausages, salt cod, braised meat, game, roast veal, meringues, biscuits, baked fruit, etc. are all great candidates for this electric oven's classic function.</p><p></p><p><strong>Damp Static Regular Cooking</strong></p><p>Standard static cooking gets even more wet with this.</p><p></p><p><strong>Cooking with Multiple Fans</strong></p><p>Lasagna, croissants and brioches, tarts, cakes, etc. can all be baked at the same time without blending aromas thanks to this feature, which also helps to save power and time.</p><p></p><p><strong>Fan Cooking with Multiple Moist Fans</strong></p><p>This increases the amount of moisture in a standard multi-fan oven.</p><p></p><p><strong>Making Sustainable Foods</strong></p><p>With the ECO function, cooking times adapt to slow roasting, like braised meats, white meats, baked pasta, delicate pastries, and so on. This cooking cycle is not meant for frozen foods, but it does allow for significant savings on electricity consumption.</p><p></p><p><strong>The 65th Proposition in California</strong></p><p>Caution: Danger to Health and Fertility</p><p><a href=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/.\\\" rel=\\\"noopener\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">Visit www.P65Warnings.ca.gov for more information.</a></p></div> <div><div> <div> <video controls=\\\"\\\" preload=\\\"auto\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/qIZ8MSDCu-Y.mp4\\\" style=\\\"max-width:320px; margin-bottom:1.2rem;\\\">There is a problem with the video tag in your browser.</video> </div> <div> <video controls=\\\"\\\" preload=\\\"auto\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/RRQlYvQPAMg.mp4\\\" style=\\\"max-width:320px; margin-bottom:1.2rem;\\\">There is a problem with the video tag in your browser.</video> </div> <div> <video controls=\\\"\\\" preload=\\\"auto\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/Uh_EEzfUhUU.mp4\\\" style=\\\"max-width:320px; margin-bottom:1.2rem;\\\">The video tag is not supported by your browser.</video> </div> <div> <video contro