ES4053008030006_p16237-1.jpg\\\" width=\\\"115\\\"/></div><div>ILVE ES4053008030006 Drip Pan For Standard Oven</div><span><bdi><span>$</span>130.00</bdi></span></a></div><div><a href=\\\"/search?q=ilve+g00201\\\"><div><img loading=\\\"lazy\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/G00201_p16239-1.jpg\\\" width=\\\"115\\\"/></div><div>ILVE G/002/01 Stainless Steel Bain-Marie (Double Boiler) for Hot Water Bath</div><span><bdi><span>$</span>382.00</bdi></span></a></div><div><a href=\\\"/search?q=ilve+g00202\\\"><div><img loading=\\\"lazy\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/G00202_p16240-1.jpg\\\" width=\\\"115\\\"/></div><div>ILVE G/002/02 Steam Cooker Basins</div><span><bdi><span>$</span>452.00</bdi></span></a></div><div><a href=\\\"/search?q=ilve+g04001\\\"><div><img loading=\\\"lazy\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/G04001_p16241-1.jpg\\\" width=\\\"115\\\"/></div><div>ILVE G/040/01 Griddle Dome</div><span><bdi><span>$</span>245.00</bdi></span></a></div><div><a href=\\\"/search?q=ilve+g4221208\\\"><div><img loading=\\\"lazy\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/G4221208_p16378-1.jpg\\\" width=\\\"115\\\"/></div><div>ILVE G4221208 Scroll Claw Leg (Sold by Individual Leg) (Chrome)</div><span><bdi><span>$</span>242.00</bdi></span></a></div><div><a href=\\\"/search?q=ilve+kgset001\\\"><div><img loading=\\\"lazy\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/KGSET001_p20076.jpg\\\" width=\\\"115\\\"/></div><div>ILVE KGSET001 Total Extension Glide Racks</div><span><bdi><span>$</span>168.00</bdi></span></a></div></div> </div> </div> </div> \", \"Option1 Name\": \"Color\", \"Option1 Value\": \"Blue Grey\", \"Option2 Name\": \"Trim\", \"Option2 Value\": \"Brass\", \"Option3 Name\": \"Oven Door Type\", \"Option3 Value\": \"Solid Door\"}, {\"Variant Name\": \"ILVE - 40 inch Majestic II Induction Range with 6 Elements, Booster Function, Bridge Control, Residual Heat Indicator (Blue Grey / Copper / Solid Door) - UMDI10QNS3BGP\", \"Variant SKU\": \"UMDI10QNS3BGP\", \"Variant Image\": \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/UMDI10QNS3BGP_p13669.jpg\", \"Variant All Images\": [\"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/UMDI10QNS3BGP_p13669.jpg\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/UMDI10QNS3BGP_p13669_173411.png\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/UMDI10QNS3BGP_p13669_173412.png\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/UMDI10QNS3BGP_p13669_173413.png\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/UMDI10QNS3BGP_p13669_11430.jpg\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/UMDI10QNS3BGP_p13669_11431.jpg\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/UMDI10QNS3BGP_p13669_11432.jpg\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/UMDI10QNS3BGP_p13669_11433.jpg\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/UMDI10QNS3BGP_p13669_33150.jpg\"], \"Variant Price\": \"10690.00\", \"Variant Barcode\": \"8051202236898\", \"Variant URLS\": \"\", \"Variant Count\": \"\", \"Variant HTML\": \" <div aria-hidden=\\\"true\\\" aria-labelledby=\\\"station-tabs-tab_description\\\" class=\\\"station-tabs-tabpanel station-tabs-default-tabpanel\\\" id=\\\"station-tabs-tabpanel_description\\\" role=\\\"tabpanel\\\"> <div class=\\\"station-tabs-tabcontent\\\"><div class=\\\"station-tabs-tabcontent\\\"><p>The 40-inch Majestic induction range is a perfect example of how traditional Italian design can coexist with modern technology. It has six efficient element zones, two total oven capacities of 2.3 and 1.52 cubic feet, a 4.3-inch full-touch control display, and an enamel oven cavity that is easy to clean.</p><p>Product Status: Available</p><div><p><strong>Majestic</strong></p><p>This show-stopping range cooker will be the focal point of your kitchen.</p><p></p><p>Majestic is a freestanding statement-piece that effortlessly integrates into any space while commanding attention with its striking combination of form and function. Its design draws inspiration from the world of professional cooking and features rounded lines, crafted details, fine finishes, and solutions and technologies that are both practical and aesthetically pleasing.</p><p></p><p>The sculpted, meticulously detailed forms of majestic range cookers, crafted from pure steel, make them eye-catching kitchen appliances that also serve as decorative accents.</p><p></p><p>These are the real deal, hand-picked gems of professional design for your home kitchen. They come in a variety of sizes (from 30 to 60 inches) and offer a plethora of set-up options, as well as RAL Classic shades upon request and fine metallic finishes.</p><p></p><ul><li>Detector of remaining heat</li><li>Scheduler with built-in timeout</li><li>Control of bridges</li><li>Function that boosts</li><li>Handles for sliding</li><li>Protecting children</li><li>Widescreen 4.3-inch</li><li>Emergency measures for overheating and liquid spills</li><li>Electronic temperature control with pinpoint accuracy</li><li>Cabinet and door soft-closing mechanism</li><li>Fast start</li></ul><p></p><hr/><p></p><p><strong>Innovations in Product Technologies</strong></p><p></p><p>Not only is aesthetics important, but having the best technologies available is essential for cooking well and enjoying oneself. ILVE puts its research and experience to work for you, providing solutions that combine top-level performance with maximum simplicity, safety, and user-friendliness, guaranteeing the best satisfaction at all times.</p><p></p><p><strong>Technologies related to stovetops</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>Induction Range (Oven)</strong></p><p>With their modern technology and elegant design, Majestic induction cooktops (hobs) make cooking a breeze. Induction facilitates the preparation of dishes and recipes with its many benefits, including safety, ease of cleaning, energy savings, and versatile temperature control and cooking speed.</p><p></p><p><strong>Measurement of Persistent Heat</strong></p><p>The glass is hot, so be careful not to touch it or put anything on it; doing so could cause damage.</p><p></p><p><strong>Automatically Stops the Timer</strong></p><p>Once the specified time has passed, the active zone is disabled.</p><p></p><p><strong>Managing Bridges</strong></p><p>If your induction cooktop (hob) has this capability, you can treat two adjacent zones as one and use a single command to control them both.</p><p></p><p><strong>Enhancement Role</strong></p><p>Makes it possible to concentrate the entire induction burner's power on a specific area, allowing you to boil and cook food more quickly.</p><p></p><p><strong>Slide Management</strong></p><p>For instance, you can adjust the operating temperature simply by gliding your finger from right to left or left to right thanks to this convenient \\\"touch control\\\" system.</p><p></p><p><strong>Protecting Children</strong></p><p>After you enable this feature, you can't use the controls to turn on the induction cooktop (hob).</p><p></p><p><strong>Preventing Liquid Spills and Overheating</strong></p><p>An automatic shutoff mechanism activates in the event of a liquid spill or overheating of the cooktop (hob).</p><p></p><hr/><p></p><p><strong>The Oven Guys</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>Impressive Size and Power: The Ovens.</strong></p><p>Our 40-inch range offers an oven capacity of up to 4 cubic feet, so you'll have plenty of room for even the largest of dishes with any combination oven, single or double.</p><p></p><p><strong>Accurate Electronic Regulation of Temperature</strong></p><p>The oven's temperature stays consistent throughout thanks to the electronic control, unlike with traditional ovens.</p><p></p><p><strong>Full-Screen 4.3-Inch Display</strong></p><p>Displaying every function with clear and immediate graphics, the display guarantees superior readability thanks to TFT technology.</p><p></p><p><strong>TFT Screen; Easy to Use, Extensive, and High-Resolution.</strong></p><p>All the controls for the oven, including temperature, timer, and automatic start/end programming, are conveniently located on the large display, so all you need is a single finger to operate either the single oven or both ovens simultaneously.</p><p></p><p><strong>Silent Closing Door System</strong></p><p>With the shock absorber installed in the door hinges, closing the door is a more gradual and noiseless process.</p><p></p><p><strong>Soft-Closing Mechanism for the Warming Drawer</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>Food Preparation Testing Device</strong></p><p>The tool you need to check the internal temperature of meat, among other things.</p><p></p><p><strong>Steam Ejection (Hot Food Preparation)</strong></p><p>The vapors are drawn out of the cavity by this system, so you can control the moisture level during cooking, giving you crispy baked dishes or juicy roasts.</p><p></p><p><strong>Heat range: 85 to 575 degrees Fahrenheit</strong></p><p>Whether you're proofing, cooking, roasting, or cooking at a low temperature, an ILVE oven can make even the most difficult recipes taste delicious.</p><p></p><p><strong>Thoroughly Inspiring Cooling Air and Dense Insulation</strong></p><p>Shields kitchen and oven-related furniture from dangerously high temperatures.</p><p></p><p><strong>Effortless Cleaning with the Folding Grill Coil</strong></p><p>You can clean the top part of the cavity more easily thanks to the articulated support, which allows you to lower the electric heating element of the grill.</p><p></p><p><strong>Dishwasher Safe Enamel</strong></p><p>Grease is easier to remove since it does not adhere to the surface.</p><p></p><p><strong>Central Oven Operations. UOV 60 E3 TFT S</strong></p><p></p><ul><li>Pizza party</li><li>Removing From Freeze</li><li>Prolonged cooking</li><li>Getting started quickly</li><li>Extensive cooking with moisture</li><li>The cooking method of the fan grill</li><li>Cooking on the grill with the door closed</li><li>Aerial cuisine</li><li>Cooking with moisture from above</li><li>Starting with the base</li><li>Cooking with moisture from below</li><li>Standard, unchanging cooking</li><li>Damp static regular cooking</li><li>Using a number of fans to cook</li><li>Various wet fan cooking methods</li><li>Sustainable cuisine</li></ul><p></p><p><strong>Additional Oven Purposes. UOV 30 E3 TFT</strong></p><p></p><ul><li>Grilling in a covered area</li><li>Aerial cuisine</li><li>Using the ground up</li><li>Regular, static cooking</li><li>Sustainable cuisine</li></ul><hr/><p></p><p><strong>Party Pizza</strong></p><p>The lower heating element, in conjunction with the other, less powerful heating elements, produces the ideal temperature and baking conditions for pizza, bread, and focaccia.</p><p></p><p><strong>Removing From Freeze</strong></p><p>Guarantees rapid thawing of any and all frozen foods, bringing them to room temperature without changing their flavor or texture.</p><p></p><p><strong>Cooking to the Extremes</strong></p><p>For foods that require a crispy finish, such as baked potatoes and veggies, chicken, salt-crusted fish, etc., this steam-discharge method guarantees rapid and intense cooking.</p><p></p><p><strong>Easy Beginning</strong></p><p>Get it to the temperature you want quickly with the fast preheating feature, then select the cooking mode that's going to work best with your food. When set to low, it can also defrost quickly.</p><p></p><p><strong>Thoroughly Moist Cooking</strong></p><p>For moist cooking, such as braised meat, stewed rabbit, salt cod, chicken cacciatore, etc., it ensures rapid and intense cooking with steam block.</p><p></p><p><strong>Searing on a Fan Grill</strong></p><p>This function is great for a wide variety of foods because it is quick, deep, and uses a lot of energy. Some examples of these foods are sausages, pork or mixed kebabs, game, Roman-style gnocchi, and pork chops.</p><p></p><p><strong>Grilling in a Room with No Doors Open</strong></p><p>Ideal for searing fillets, Florentine steaks, fish, and even veggies quickly and thoroughly, as well as browning and roasting meat in general.</p><p></p><p><strong>Recipes from the Sky</strong></p><p>This function is perfect for browning and finishing a wide variety of foods; burgers, pork chops, veal steaks, sole, cuttlefish, etc. benefit greatly from it.</p><p></p><p><strong>Elevated Recipes for Moist Food</strong></p><p>Great for browning and giving a variety of foods that last splash of color a little more color without making them tough.</p><p></p><p><strong>Lessons in Home Cooking</strong></p><p>Pastries (such as biscuits, meringues, leavened desserts, fruit desserts, and so on) are best cooked in this way to finish the cooking cycle.</p><p></p><p><strong>In-Depth Recipes for Moist Food</strong></p><p>To finish the cooking cycle with the correct amount of moisture, this is the best way to do it.</p><p></p><p><strong>Standard, Static Cooking</strong></p><p>Pork chops, sausages, salt cod, braised meat, game, roast veal, meringues, biscuits, baked fruit, etc. are all great candidates for this electric oven's classic function.</p><p></p><p><strong>Normal Cooking with Moist Static</strong></p><p>This makes traditional static cooking even more moist.</p><p></p><p><strong>Cooking with Multiple Fans</strong></p><p>You can bake a variety of foods at once without worrying about their aromas blending\\u2014lasagna, croissants and brioches, tarts, cakes, etc.\\u2014and save both time and energy thanks to this feature.</p><p></p><p><strong>A Variety of Moist Fan Recipes</strong></p><p>This increases the amount of moisture in a standard multi-fan oven.</p><p></p><p><strong>Ecology in the Kitchen</strong></p><p>Slow roasting foods, like braised meats, white meats, baked pasta, and delicate pastries, necessitate longer cooking times when using the ECO function, which significantly reduces power consumption. However, this cooking cycle is not meant for foods that are frozen.</p><p></p><p><strong>Proposition 65 in California\\u2014</strong></p><p>Caution: Potential Risks to Health and Fertility</p><p><a href=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/.\\\" rel=\\\"noopener\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">V