\\"/></div><div>ILVE G4221208 Scroll Claw Leg (Sold by Individual Leg) (Chrome)</div><span><bdi><span>$</span>242.00</bdi></span></a></div><div><a href=\\\"/search?q=ilve+kgset001\\\"><div><img loading=\\\"lazy\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/KGSET001_p20076.jpg\\\" width=\\\"115\\\"/></div><div>ILVE KGSET001 Total Extension Glide Racks</div><span><bdi><span>$</span>168.00</bdi></span></a></div></div> </div> </div> </div> \", \"Option1 Name\": \"Color\", \"Option1 Value\": \"Glossy Black\", \"Option2 Name\": \"Trim\", \"Option2 Value\": \"Chrome\", \"Option3 Name\": \"Oven Door Type\", \"Option3 Value\": \"Solid Door\"}, {\"Variant Name\": \"ILVE - 40 inch Majestic II Induction Range with 6 Elements, Booster Function, Bridge Control, Residual Heat Indicator (Glossy Black / Brass / Solid Door) - UMDI10QNS3BKG\", \"Variant SKU\": \"UMDI10QNS3BKG\", \"Variant Image\": \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/UMDI10QNS3BKG_p13695.jpg\", \"Variant All Images\": [\"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/UMDI10QNS3BKG_p13695.jpg\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/UMDI10QNS3BKG_p13695_173420.png\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/UMDI10QNS3BKG_p13695_173421.png\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/UMDI10QNS3BKG_p13695_173422.png\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/UMDI10QNS3BKG_p13695_11442.jpg\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/UMDI10QNS3BKG_p13695_11443.jpg\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/UMDI10QNS3BKG_p13695_11444.jpg\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/UMDI10QNS3BKG_p13695_11445.jpg\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/UMDI10QNS3BKG_p13695_33153.jpg\"], \"Variant Price\": \"10690.00\", \"Variant Barcode\": \"8051202220354\", \"Variant URLS\": \"\", \"Variant Count\": \"\", \"Variant HTML\": \" <div aria-hidden=\\\"true\\\" aria-labelledby=\\\"station-tabs-tab_description\\\" class=\\\"station-tabs-tabpanel station-tabs-default-tabpanel\\\" id=\\\"station-tabs-tabpanel_description\\\" role=\\\"tabpanel\\\"> <div class=\\\"station-tabs-tabcontent\\\"><div class=\\\"station-tabs-tabcontent\\\"><p>The 40-inch Majestic induction range is a perfect example of how traditional Italian design can coexist with modern technology. It has six efficient element zones, two total oven capacities of 2.3 and 1.52 cubic feet, a 4.3-inch full-touch control display, and an enamel oven cavity that is easy to clean.</p><p>Order now for delivery in 90 to 120 days!</p><div><p><strong>Majestic</strong></p><p>The show-stopping range cooker that will turn your kitchen into a showpiece.</p><p></p><p>Majestic, a freestanding statement-piece with a style that incorporates rounded lines, crafted details, fine finishes, solutions, and technologies derived from the world of professional cooking, is a beautiful and functional fusion of form and function. It effortlessly blends into any setting while still taking center stage.</p><p></p><p>The graceful curves and meticulously crafted details of majestic range cookers make them beautiful additions to any home.</p><p></p><p>These are the real deal, hand-picked gems of professional design for your home kitchen. They come in a variety of sizes (from 30 to 60 inches) and offer a plethora of set-up options, as well as RAL Classic shades upon request and fine metallic finishes.</p><p></p><ul><li>Detector of residual heat</li><li>Timer with built-in self-exclusion</li><li>Control of bridges</li><li>Enhancement feature</li><li>Controls that slide</li><li>Preventing harm to children</li><li>Retina 4.3-inch touchscreen</li><li>Prevention of overheating and liquid spills</li><li>Accurate electronic regulation of temperature</li><li>Cabinet and door soft-closing mechanism</li><li>Fast start</li></ul><p></p><hr/><p></p><p><strong>Technology for Products</strong></p><p></p><p>Not only is aesthetics important, but having the best technologies available is essential for cooking well and enjoying oneself. ILVE puts its research and experience to work for you, providing solutions that guarantee the best satisfaction by combining top-level performance with maximum simplicity, safety, and user-friendliness.</p><p></p><p><strong>Technologies related to stovetops</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>Induction Range (Oven)</strong></p><p>Majestic induction cooktops (hobs) are a modern, practical, and safe method of cooking that combines cutting-edge technology with an elegant and modern aesthetic. Induction offers many benefits, such as safety, ease of cleaning, energy savings, and versatile temperature control and cooking speed, all of which make it easier to prepare dishes and recipes.</p><p></p><p><strong>Measurement of Persistent Heat</strong></p><p>The glass is hot, so be careful not to touch it or put anything on it; doing so could cause damage.</p><p></p><p><strong>Timer with Built-In Stop Function</strong></p><p>Once the specified time has passed, the active zone is disabled.</p><p></p><p><strong>Control of Bridges</strong></p><p>If your induction cooktop (hob) has this capability, you can treat two adjacent zones as one and use a single command to control them both.</p><p></p><p><strong>Enhanced Capability</strong></p><p>Helps you boil water and cook food more quickly by directing the full power of the induction hob to a specific zone.</p><p></p><p><strong>Slide Management</strong></p><p>By simply gliding your finger from side to side, you can adjust the operating temperature, for instance, thanks to this convenient \\\"touch control\\\" system.</p><p></p><p><strong>Protection of Children</strong></p><p>The induction cooktop (hob) cannot be turned on using the controls once this feature has been enabled and will remain so until disabled.</p><p></p><p><strong>Safety from Overheating and Liquid Spills</strong></p><p>A safety feature is installed to cut power in the event that the stovetop (hob) gets too hot or a spillage occurs.</p><p></p><hr/><p></p><p><strong>The Oven Guys</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>Impressive Size and Power: The Ovens.</strong></p><p>No matter if you're cooking a single or double combination oven\\u2014with a capacity of up to 4 cubic feet\\u2014our 40-inch range will give you more than enough room, even for your largest dishes.</p><p></p><p><strong>Accurate Electronic Regulation of Temperature</strong></p><p>Unlike with traditional ovens, the temperature of the oven will stay consistent thanks to the electronic control.</p><p></p><p><strong>Full-Screen 4.3-Inch Display</strong></p><p>Displaying every function with clear and immediate graphics, the display guarantees superior readability thanks to TFT technology.</p><p></p><p><strong>Our TFT display is designed to be user-friendly, comprehensive, and high resolution.</strong></p><p>All the controls for the oven, including temperature, timer, and automatic start/end programming, are conveniently located on the large display, so all you need is a single finger to operate either the single oven or both ovens simultaneously.</p><p></p><p><strong>Doors with a Gentle Closing Mechanism</strong></p><p>A shock absorber is integrated into the door hinges, allowing for a quieter and more gradual closing.</p><p></p><p><strong>Cabinet with Warming Drawer and Soft-Closing Mechanism</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>The Cooking Probe</strong></p><p>A must-have tool for taking internal temperatures, such as those of meat slices.</p><p></p><p><strong>Steam Ejection (Hot Food Preparation)</strong></p><p>A crispy baked dish or a soft and juicy roast can be achieved with the help of this system, which removes the vapors from inside the cavity and allows you to choose between a drier or more moist cooking.</p><p></p><p><strong>Range of temperatures: 85 to 575 degrees Fahrenheit</strong></p><p>You can effortlessly and perfectly prepare even the most intricate and sophisticated recipes in an ILVE oven, whether you're proofing, cooking, roasting, or using low heat.</p><p></p><p><strong>Airflow for Tangential Cooling and High-Density Insulation</strong></p><p>Shields kitchen and oven-related furniture from dangerously high temperatures.</p><p></p><p><strong>Effortless Cleaning with the Folding Grill Coil</strong></p><p>The electric heating element of the grill can be lowered for easier cleaning of the top part of the cavity, thanks to the articulated support.</p><p></p><p><strong>Rinse-Free Enamel</strong></p><p>Because the grease doesn't adhere to the surface, it's easier to clean.</p><p></p><p><strong>Key Oven Responsibilities. UOV 60 E3 TFT S</strong></p><p></p><ul><li>The pizza party</li><li>Removing from Freeze</li><li>Prolonged cooking</li><li>Fast start</li><li>Extremely moist cooking</li><li>Cooking with a fan grill</li><li>Cooking on the grill with the door closed</li><li>Recipes viewed from above</li><li>Steaming food cooked in the air</li><li>An Underground Kitchen</li><li>Steaming food from below</li><li>Regular, static cooking</li><li>Cooking that is moist and static</li><li>Numerous fan-assisted cooking methods</li><li>Various wet fan cooking methods</li><li>Green food preparation</li></ul><p></p><p><strong>Functions of the Secondary Oven. UOV 30 E3 TFT</strong></p><p></p><ul><li>Cooking on the grill with the door closed</li><li>Aerial cuisine</li><li>Using the ground up</li><li>Regular, static cooking</li><li>Sustainable cuisine</li></ul><hr/><p></p><p><strong>A Pizza Party</strong></p><p>The lower heating element, in conjunction with the other, less powerful heating elements, produces the ideal temperature and baking conditions for pizza, bread, and focaccia.</p><p></p><p><strong>Removing from Freeze</strong></p><p>Guarantees rapid thawing of any and all frozen foods, bringing them to room temperature without changing their flavor or texture.</p><p></p><p><strong>Cooking to the Extremes</strong></p><p>For foods that require a crispy finish, such as baked potatoes and veggies, chicken, salt-crusted fish, etc., this steam-discharge method guarantees rapid and intense cooking.</p><p></p><p><strong>Easy Beginning</strong></p><p>Quick preheating gets the oven to the temperature you want it to be in no time at all, and then you can select the cooking mode that's going to work best with your food. When set to a low temperature, it can also defrost food quickly.</p><p></p><p><strong>Thoroughly Moist Cooking</strong></p><p>For moist cooking, such as braised meat, stewed rabbit, salt cod, chicken cacciatore, etc., it ensures rapid and intense cooking with steam block.</p><p></p><p><strong>Searing on a Fan Grill</strong></p><p>Many foods, including sausages, pork or mixed kebabs, game, Roman-style gnocchi, etc., can be cooked quickly and thoroughly with this function, which also significantly reduces energy consumption.</p><p></p><p><strong>Methods for Grilling with a Closed Door</strong></p><p>Ideal for searing fillets, Florentine steaks, fish, and even veggies quickly and thoroughly, as well as browning and roasting meat in general.</p><p></p><p><strong>Elevated Cooking</strong></p><p>Burgers, pork chops, veal steaks, sole, cuttlefish, etc., all benefit from browning and the finishing touch of color that this function provides.</p><p></p><p><strong>Heavenly, Moist Recipes</strong></p><p>Perfect for turning many foods a golden brown while keeping them soft in the middle.</p><p></p><p><strong>Lessons in Home Cooking</strong></p><p>If you're making pastries (biscuits, meringues, leavened desserts, fruit desserts, etc.), this is the best way to finish the cooking cycle.</p><p></p><p><strong>In-Depth Recipes for Moist Food</strong></p><p>In order to finish the cooking cycle with the correct amount of moisture, this is the best way to do it.</p><p></p><p><strong>Standard, Static Cooking</strong></p><p>Electric ovens typically have this one setting that works well for things like roast veal, pork chops, sausages, salt cod, braised meat, game, meringues, biscuits, baked fruit, and more.</p><p></p><p><strong>Normal Cooking with Moist Static</strong></p><p>Typical static cooking gets even more wet with this.</p><p></p><p><strong>Multi-Fan Oven Utilization</strong></p><p>Lasagna, croissants and brioches, tarts, cakes, etc. can all be baked at the same time without blending aromas thanks to this feature, which also helps to save power and time.</p><p></p><p><strong>A Variety of Moist Fan Recipes</strong></p><p>When cooking with multiple fans, this increases the moisture content.</p><p></p><p><strong>Sustainable Food Preparation</strong></p><p>Slow roasting foods, like braised meats, white meats, baked pasta, and delicate pastries, necessitate longer cooking times when using the ECO function, which significantly reduces power consumption. However, this cooking cycle is not meant for foods that are frozen.</p><p></p><p><strong>The 65th Proposition in California</strong></p><p>Health Risks: Cancer and Fertility Impairment</p><p><a href=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/.\\\" rel=\\\"noopener\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">For more information, visit www.P65Warnings.ca.gov.</a></p></div> <div><div> <div> <video controls=\\\"\\\" preload=\\\"auto\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/qIZ8MSDCu-Y.mp4\\\" style=\\\"max-width:320px; margin-bottom:1.2rem;\\\">Sorry, but the video tag isn't compatible with your browser.</video> </div> <div> <video controls=\\\"\\\" preload=\\\"auto\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/RRQlYvQPAMg.mp4\\\" style=\\\"max-width:320px; margin-bottom:1.2rem;\\\">The video tag is not supported by your browser.</video> </div> <div> <video controls=\\\"\\\" preload=\\\"auto\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/Uh_EEzfUhUU.mp4\\\" style=\\\"max-width:320px; margin-bottom:1.2rem;\\\">Sorry, but the video tag isn't compatible with your browser.</video> </div> <div> <video controls=\\\"\\\" preload=\\\"auto\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/wKi6ZYNcCxY.mp4\\\" style=\\\"max-width:320px; margin-bottom:1.2rem;\\\">The video tag is not supported by your browser.</video> </div> <div> <video controls=\\\"\\\" preload=\\\"auto\\\" s